cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of finding equivalent reformulations of SQL queries, which is a fundamental problem in database systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DB (Databases). The paper also involves logical reasoning and equivalence tests, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Additionally, the paper discusses aggregation and grouping, which are topics in artificial intelligence and machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves algorithmic techniques and complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
